messages.content: again interested to see the discussion on this

I've tried to build around this card a lot, its always felt underwhelming. Automation doesnt really have a need for a slow scaling card thats also shuffling mediocre damage cards into your deck just to ramp up.

if I'm looking to just have a bunch of functions, I think <infinite beams> works just better. It does 5 free damage per power played, (or 7 with an upgrade which puts infinite blades to shame) and costs zero which lets you spam out functions; it will make you weaker in the endgame but before that its pretty strong at getting you through the rest of the game

embeds.title: Infinite Beams
embeds.description:
Uncommon Power / 1 :e_automaton: / The Automaton

At the start of each turn, gain a Minor Beam. (+.)

messages.content: you can pair infinite loop with beam, which I think is the intention, but often I find that the enemy is just dead before loop scales up enough to outdo another function that deals damage (like separator or terminator)

I think Automation just has a pretty poor rare pool in general, lots of effects that are hard to put into a deck and don't usually do anything too crazy (like ship it taking 50 years to scale and being worse then bug barrage)
fortunately, automation has the best common card pool which is worth a lot more for the character's viability overall.
Auto's uncommons are also dope
yeah, i have similar feelings, I think during most of the run I'd just *much* rather have a virus spamming out minor beams
Virus is giga busted, that card and dev tools carries automations rare pool
Summon Orb?
Find and Replace is also generally good

find and replace is good; basically a seek that works if you draw it at the bottom of your deck. Its nothing crazy though, like seek its not going to break your deck just make it stronger. Summon orb is fine; just fine. I like it in function spam decks but i'm taking it at about the same rate as a card like juggernaut
I've heard a lot of cries for Summon Orb to get nerfed

I dont see how summon orb is that problematic and not cards like infinite beams  and virus which make it able to proc multiple times a turn. Most of the time when the card is only being used once a turn it just feels fine
the problem is that it's giving you a pretty hefty bonus for something you're doing already as automaton, and you can lean into it super hard once you have it
it's both a damage engine and a block engine in 1 card

4 block a turn isnt really anything insane for a rare card. Consider that full release can do things like draw 5 additional cards at the start of your turn; or give you infinite blur (homemade barricade that also can do 1 more thing)
now when its giving like 30 block and killing the enemy because you played virus, then thats pretty great but virus is doing a lot of the work in that combo
you get the bonus on creating and playing a function - at the very least it's 8 per turn, and if you lean into it 16 isn't that far-fetched
and that's without upgrading

well you do upgrade the card every time, so saying numbers like 4 isnt that accurate. I don't see it being the best rare card my deck could have very often (it also doesn't pair well with status decks). Often when I see the card being very strong; its because my deck can make the most out of the card but thats not always applicable
